			<ns0:name>robertm@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/robertm@google.com/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">In tests/debug_stub/debugger_test.c using:

void test_interrupt() {
  int x = 0;
  for (;;) {
    x = (x + 1) % 2;
  }
}

causes segfaults, while this worked:

volatile int x = 0;
void test_interrupt() {
  for (;;) {
    x = (x + 1) % 2;
  }
}




